casebody.data:
Edward J. Canavan v. Louise C. Canavan

Wynne, C. J., Baldwin, Daly, King and Murphy, Js.

Argued February 4 decided February 13, 1958 William K. Lawlor, for the appellant (defendant). Michael V. Blansfield, for the appellee (plaintiff). Per Curiam.

The finding, which is not subject to material correction, amply supports the judgment. Gowdy v. Gowdy, 120 Conn. 508, 510, 181 A. 462; Medvedow v. Medvedow, 140 Conn. 698, 700, 103 A.2d 337.

There is no error.
